        '1. Scope of Work:\n* Responsible for the full spectrum of general human resource function including compensation & benefits, recruitment, employee relations, training & development...etc \n* Co-ordinate planning, implementation and monitoring of all Human Resource management systems, policies and procedure \n* Responsible for the full spectrum of general office management and administration function\n* Develop and implement policies and procedures on office management and administration\n* To perform projects as needed and provide HR and Administration support on issues\n\n2. Compensation and Benefit:\n* Participation in the formulation of planning to pay and welfare plan, adjust the compensation process, regularly collect market salary information and data for reference; \n* Master the related compensation and benefits policies, making all kinds of salary report, data management, and salary related files; \n* Organise complete company performance evaluation criteria system, according to the problems in the implement and effect, provide suggestions for solutions, and establish company flow and promotion system.\n\n3. Recruitment:\n* Communicate manpower needs with each department timely, set up recruitment strategy and plan \n* Implement recruiting process according to planning and ensure the efficiency and effectiveness of recruitment activity \n* Develop and maintain suitable recruitment channels\n\n4. Employees Relation/Communication:\n* Responsible for staff on-board process, coordinate with Fesco\n* Responsible for staff probation, contract extension, exit process\n* Conduct exit interview for resigned employee\n* Coordinate with departments for the annual employee evaluation\n* Conduct employee focus groups, grievances handling and conducting employee satisfaction survey \n* Explain to employees all HR-related issues: benefit, policies and answer to staff request\n* Be the link between Company and employees communication.\n\n5. Training and development:\n* Define & develop internal or external training module as per brand identity and needs\n* Provide advice and support to the department heads to develop appropriate and realistic career / development plans for the employees\n* Plan, coordinate and prioritize the implementation of the development plans of all employees based on the available resources.\n\n6. Office Management and Administration:\n* Develop and implement policies and procedures on office management and administration such as reception, courier, travelling, office cleaning, facilities maintenance, fixed asset management, purchasing of office supply and etc.\n* Negotiate lease contract and lead the office renovation and relocation projects. Plan the office space well to balance business needs and cost effectiveness.\n* Provide clean, comfortable and safe working environment and build up a good image to visitors and customers.\n* Contact with vendors and suppliers, review performance and area for improvement.\n* Make sure office facilities well functioned\n* Budget and control office administrative cost and expense \n* Review and negotiate administration related contracts\n* Provide legal support in office administration such as preparing documents for office registration and renewal, updating upon any change\n* Assist IT Manager mange local IT Issue time to time\n* Handle ad hoc tasks and projects assigned by the management', 
        null, null, 0, null, '20161101000000999000000001', '°××ÓÑÀ', to_date('23-04-2017 13:35:24', 'dd-mm-yyyy hh24:mi:ss'), 0, null, '0', 0, null, null, null);
